item.title: Silab Notepad Code
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

Please refrain from posting titles full of capitals and spam. If you create another topic like that, I will begin to lock them.

@ Topic: A class file is the compiled version of a .java file. Java files come with the source. Most files are self-explanatory, such as NPCHandler. Take a look inside of the java files and try to read and understand what they do. Do not change the .class version of the file. The class file is written in bytecode and the bytecode is changed when you use the compiler.

You can also find tutorials on learning Java here:

http://java.sun.com/
